His response to Sanders announcing his second run last week: scrambling a trip of his own to Sioux City and Des Moines.
The senator’s campaign probably would have been open to that and to the buzz it would have produced about the strength of his 2020 campaign.
“It’s a very personal reality,” de Blasio explained to reporters about his decision to come to Iowa on Saturday.
He didn’t have a timetable for deciding whether he would run, he added on Sunday.
“There is plenty of money in this world, there is plenty of money in this country—it’s just in the wrong hands,” he said.